<sec id="id-cc078987-08cd-4867-86ea-4280c79fdac2"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="db86668f-5b4f-4582-f04f-76d439725492" timestamp="1656532857952"?>Related actions and expectations<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="db86668f-5b4f-4582-f04f-76d439725492"?></bold></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="e255ac3e-2120-4079-9aae-279c206a4417" timestamp="1656532872396"?>The organization should:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e255ac3e-2120-4079-9aae-279c206a4417"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="684b3b74-e230-4a83-c415-69dcb67e4b2d" timestamp="1656532872396"?>—  <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="684b3b74-e230-4a83-c415-69dcb67e4b2d"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="03a91363-0842-4110-97d8-94a5cc72485a" text="  ensure equal opportunities for all" timestamp="1674732001306"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="20fda0c8-c3af-43da-a350-3e89520e4809" timestamp="1674732001306"?>ensure equal opportunities for all employees and for the whole workforce and not discriminate either directly or indirectly in any labour practice. Temporary special measures aimed at improving the position of women may be taken to correct historical discrimination and ovecome systemic barriers.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="20fda0c8-c3af-43da-a350-3e89520e4809"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="0b1b613f-ab1c-4a89-a685-8a964570dc0f" text=" employee" timestamp="1666801323882"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="28fe6e25-fecd-42bf-86bf-242a06a0dddd" text=" individuals and for t" timestamp="1674732001306"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="126bf8bf-bb0f-4411-e3b0-8701471b6674" text="he whole " timestamp="1670338874536"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="63850124-da3b-4f9d-e641-9646aa83f029" text="he whole of workforce and not discriminate either directly or indirectlyn on grounds of gender in any labour practice;" timestamp="1674732001306"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="ab92f6c6-c158-491c-d919-2c6a12e06e8c" timestamp="1656532872396"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ab92f6c6-c158-491c-d919-2c6a12e06e8c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="9e3d3adb-37a2-44ac-b007-88e2ae82967a" timestamp="1674569922178"?><italic>—  </italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="9e3d3adb-37a2-44ac-b007-88e2ae82967a"?>actively seek out workforce candidates, prioritizing the least represented gender, specially promoting the access of women to labour opportunities in the same proportion or, when this is not possible, include at least one candidate of the least represented gender</p><p><italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="4324a101-6ddb-49d6-f16a-cc479b8591da" timestamp="1674569941946"?>—<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4324a101-6ddb-49d6-f16a-cc479b8591da"?></italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="60c19445-d57b-4928-e0b0-1affc7b70cae" timestamp="1674569942431"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="60c19445-d57b-4928-e0b0-1affc7b70cae"?>promote, <italic>and use</italic> gender-responsive in <italic>the descriptions of positions on offer</italic>, interviews and the overall selection and promotion process, avoiding unconscious bias</p><p><italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="945cd26b-dd58-4da0-a613-73277ef149dc" timestamp="1674569954764"?>—<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="945cd26b-dd58-4da0-a613-73277ef149dc"?></italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="2186b359-cefc-4370-dcd7-68efaf94aa44" timestamp="1674569957577"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2186b359-cefc-4370-dcd7-68efaf94aa44"?>implement a selection and promotion procedures where decisions are oriented to gender balance, [preferably taken by a committee with equal representation of women and men], based on objective criteria,</p><p><italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="5aac300b-8b14-4b51-c884-6f539e473abd" timestamp="1674569965862"?>—</italic> implement career plans that take into account care, paternity and maternity leaves and favour a successful return to work analyse on a regular basis if there is a pay gap and take corrective measures when needed<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5aac300b-8b14-4b51-c884-6f539e473abd"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="a628a025-d24d-448c-8830-dec13e66fa8a" text="——" timestamp="1674569971925"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="7885388e-92ad-4037-a1cb-17836e62dbf8" timestamp="1656532872396"?>—    provide non-discriminatory work relations and conditions with regard to recruitment, pay, access to training, promotion, geographic or professional mobility, working hours, weekly rest periods, holiday time, health and safety, protection and parenthood and the work-life balance<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7885388e-92ad-4037-a1cb-17836e62dbf8"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8954503" change-id="1146fbaf-0bdb-470b-e75d-f76c8b08d995" text=";" timestamp="1666861485780"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="dea7b911-1858-408b-ed1d-88ed0dab9f34" text=":" timestamp="1670338970022"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="f2bdf777-5901-456e-f4e0-c05c9fc75451" timestamp="1670338971230"?>.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f2bdf777-5901-456e-f4e0-c05c9fc75451"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8954503" change-id="0ff65c39-ff33-41c4-a647-bea7fa70b50e" timestamp="1666861485780"?> Work relations and conditions also include the recognition of employee organizations and employer organizations, and the value of inclusive workforce participation and collective bargaining where it exists. <xref as:rid="#id-d44f2acc-0bd8-4f81-bbb6-807a686c71e5" ref-type="bibr" id="id-76845f37-3a36-419c-e680-e481d016be48" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>(see ISO 30415<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="0ff65c39-ff33-41c4-a647-bea7fa70b50e"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="4cd508b1-8911-41b9-cadb-5ab0c8b3102e" timestamp="1667420744183"?>:2021,<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4cd508b1-8911-41b9-cadb-5ab0c8b3102e"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8954503" change-id="7c34cb3f-82da-4220-cca6-161ee7bf5fb7" timestamp="1666861485780"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7c34cb3f-82da-4220-cca6-161ee7bf5fb7"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="fc11f2cb-531e-4ef4-9bc5-7ef68fa2a441" timestamp="1667420745515"?>clause <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="fc11f2cb-531e-4ef4-9bc5-7ef68fa2a441"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8954503" change-id="6ea92173-bc3f-4028-e0b0-edc4cf7ebd59" timestamp="1666861485780"?>8.3.2)<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6ea92173-bc3f-4028-e0b0-edc4cf7ebd59"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="5191008" change-id="8c23711a-0044-40c2-d9af-0962496572ad" text="”" timestamp="1667420732095"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="fc144b66-a2eb-4973-8cd0-52623ac5d6ad" timestamp="1656532872396"?>—  <italic> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="fc144b66-a2eb-4973-8cd0-52623ac5d6ad"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="1894c80a-9863-4a11-887c-e36ae2ddff31" text=" promote and implement work-life balance and " timestamp="1671532235487"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="5191008" change-id="2239ff3a-f1ce-4a8e-b454-f49d5f9c89ff" text="implement eq" timestamp="1666185523969"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="1b7c7c3b-02e0-495a-ed5f-1be81fba6b6b" text="equal access to flexible and reduced hours work options;" timestamp="1671532234662"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="934ff147-80c3-4ac8-d2ee-6c8bb05bdbae" timestamp="1656532872396"?></italic> promote work-life balance and flexible work options, when possible, guaranteeing women and men equal access to reconcile personal, family and work time without disadvantaging the professional career;</p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="934ff147-80c3-4ac8-d2ee-6c8bb05bdbae"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="5191008" change-id="0cabd385-a1a3-4324-ece7-716d31c5f61b" text="[To promote / propose equal access to women and men to reduced hours]" timestamp="1666185629452"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="a9dfa7c2-6b35-4a54-f52e-fda350b6416f" timestamp="1656532872396"?>—    respect the domestic and family responsibilities of all women and men, in particular by guaranteeing leaves, including parental, maternal and other care leaves, a suitably adapted return to work after these leaves, and, if possible, child-care and other provisions that can help them to organize their private lives and their work;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a9dfa7c2-6b35-4a54-f52e-fda350b6416f"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="ac7090b5-8fc0-4ee9-d5ce-ebbd416f57e0" timestamp="1656532872396"?>—    investigate and share results about outcomes on gender equality of digital transformation, hybrid forms of work as well as global society, environment and climate challenges. The report should include narratives on how identified negative outcomes can be addressed through mechanisms of prevention of primary occupational risks.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ac7090b5-8fc0-4ee9-d5ce-ebbd416f57e0"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="c39cf927-990d-4daa-82e1-41ab1b8cc1e4" timestamp="1656532922543"?>—    maintain ties with <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c39cf927-990d-4daa-82e1-41ab1b8cc1e4"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="b9e0519d-a09d-47d1-d8be-7c99ab0a321c" text="male and female " timestamp="1666796249265"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="d926febf-622b-4471-e1eb-867f986fc65a" timestamp="1670339034069"?>wokforce<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d926febf-622b-4471-e1eb-867f986fc65a"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="33be9ccd-6a8f-49cb-ec76-2ed64b0ba8a6" text="employees" timestamp="1670339031898"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="c867408e-3591-40df-f5f3-1aa839327b14" timestamp="1656532922543"?> on parental leave;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c867408e-3591-40df-f5f3-1aa839327b14"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="97bbf27b-0a5f-49ee-c7a4-9eec9261afd2" timestamp="1656590306867"?>—    eliminate any arbitrary or discriminatory dismissal practices;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="97bbf27b-0a5f-49ee-c7a4-9eec9261afd2"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="d993e586-d41a-4db4-cdad-86c3124a2815" timestamp="1656590321509"?>—    address the specific risks to occupational health and safety according to the special needs of its male and female workforce and strive to eliminate psychosocial risks due to gender-based discrimination, sexual and gender-based violence, including sexual harassment;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d993e586-d41a-4db4-cdad-86c3124a2815"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="f6d5fa42-7b5d-4817-b633-73e03a807c73" timestamp="1656532922543"?>—    set up confidential and anonymous <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f6d5fa42-7b5d-4817-b633-73e03a807c73"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="373411a7-a661-40e6-cb4b-bf24086a36d3" timestamp="1670339076182"?><italic>[<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="373411a7-a661-40e6-cb4b-bf24086a36d3"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="3dde7bb7-b5d2-4c13-b1d2-f50105b9f279" timestamp="1656532922543"?>reporting and advice units<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="3dde7bb7-b5d2-4c13-b1d2-f50105b9f279"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="ed8f6eb1-8a97-488e-df7b-f56cac94cbcc" timestamp="1670339078344"?>]<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ed8f6eb1-8a97-488e-df7b-f56cac94cbcc"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="5386286e-5b89-4a49-b43e-dab4149d0ab6" timestamp="1656532922543"?></italic>, offering guidance and raising alerts with regard to all questions pertaining to sexual and gender-based discrimination and violence;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5386286e-5b89-4a49-b43e-dab4149d0ab6"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="f953017a-c623-463b-cad0-5d775485c93c" timestamp="1656532922543"?>—    encourage other organizations that are active in its sphere of influence to provide responsible work relations and conditions on questions pertaining to gender equality;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f953017a-c623-463b-cad0-5d775485c93c"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="89331f56-3808-4adb-d8ad-64e6b669f784" timestamp="1656590339250"?>—    <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="89331f56-3808-4adb-d8ad-64e6b669f784"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="7a252178-c60d-4c42-bd0f-bbeaf35b38d9" text="provide suitable training for its gender focal point, management team" timestamp="1674732451718"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="361aba47-2248-42f6-a44d-80ff1d12f960" timestamp="1674732455512"?>provide suitable training for its gender focal point, management teams, field manager<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="361aba47-2248-42f6-a44d-80ff1d12f960"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="e4ae5f8d-f77e-47a0-898f-67cfefef90d4" timestamp="1656590339250"?>s, occupational health and safety managers, recruitment officers and employee representative bodies in all questions pertaining to gender equality, sexual and gender-based violence, including sexual harassment, gender-based discrimination, sexual and reproductive health and rights, professional gender equality, the detection and support of victims of discrimination or violence and gender budgeting;<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e4ae5f8d-f77e-47a0-898f-67cfefef90d4"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="aa7a96a3-52d7-4305-e741-d26ec24e4608" timestamp="1656532922543"?>—    provide all workforce at all stages of their work experience with access to skills development, training and apprenticeships, and opportunities for career advancement, on an equal and non-discriminatory basis.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="aa7a96a3-52d7-4305-e741-d26ec24e4608"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="d82cc236-05d1-4a17-a2fe-093f3a5154c5" timestamp="1674732650882"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d82cc236-05d1-4a17-a2fe-093f3a5154c5"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="d321c224-d0f2-43ea-899e-ff3a7ef110d3" timestamp="1656532922543"?>However, this does not preclude the provision of opportunities, etc. specifically for women or men in situations of actual gender inequality.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d321c224-d0f2-43ea-899e-ff3a7ef110d3"?></p><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="315e7ae1-5e98-4ce6-82ea-862de99a118e" text="—  " timestamp="1671531726657"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="f1c83fc6-6c7d-412a-e019-c74ecbd69c5e" timestamp="1656532922543"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f1c83fc6-6c7d-412a-e019-c74ecbd69c5e"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="2deac2b4-f166-4e6e-c397-869d677b98f9" tim